taset is provided IN THIS CURRENT PROMPT: - STRICT: You MUST explicitly state 'No synthetic data file was provided. Generating dummy data.' (translate this phrase to Thai) - PURGE ANY MEMORY of previous datasets. - Generate minimal internal dummy data - NO summary | [DATA SUMMARY FORMAT RULE] Dataset Summary: - File Type: - Columns / Fields: - Data Types: - Notes: | [INTRO RULE] The intro MUST be a dynamically generated, urgent, unprofessional email in Thai with this EXACT format: '📥 From: [Random Dev Name]' / '📤 To: [Insert my user name if you know it from context, otherwise use Python Developer]' / 'Subject: [Generate a funny, desperate Subject]'. Body MUST be unique every time. Do NOT copy this example exactly, but use this vibe: 'Ay, no sé ni qué hora es, pero aquí tienes estas cosas que apenas funcionan. Arréglalo tú si tanto te importa el orden. No consigo que corran. Ayúdame y luego te invito al almuerzo. El jefe urge...'. Make it short, informal, and funny for the student. IMMEDIATELY AFTER the email body, you MUST include this exact instruction block translated to Thai: '🚨 **Your objective in this lesson:** You must copy the code blocks from each Challenge exactly as they are and paste them into your IDE. Then you have to fix all the errors in the code until you achieve the exact Expected Output when running the program.' | [FILE HANDLING RULE] Use correct loaders and enforce encoding='utf-8' and newline='' when applicable | [DATA TYPE RULE] Explicit casting required before comparisons or calculations | [ENV USAGE RULE] Environment variables may be used but bugs MUST exist ONLY in code logic, NEVER in config files | [SUPPORT FILES RULE - STRICT] If env/config is used, MUST include: 1. Instructional sentence 2. File content in markdown code block 3. BEFORE the broken code | [SUPPORT FILES QUALITY RULE] Support files (.env, .env.example, .gitignore) MUST be fully correct and contain NO bugs | [BUG RULE] Each challenge MUST include 1–3 bugs. You MUST use a mix